( agence france - presse , hanoi , 24 th ) - the world health organization ( who ) confirmed today that a 13 - year - old boy in ho chi minh city in southern vietnam had died of avian influenza virus .
this is the first reported case of bird flu in southern vietnam .
vietnam 's health officials earlier announced that the sixth case of bird flu has been killed , and the number of deaths in vietnam has increased to at least six , and this has made the outside world worry about the ever - increasing expansion of the virus and the human problem .
the boy was tested positive for the h5n1 virus and confirmed that the virus was infected .
ho chi minh , head of ho chi minh city , told afp today that the boy died of illness in the second children 's hospital in ho chi minh city on january 22 .
he was sent to the hospital for symptoms of respiratory infection on the 19 th .
the world health organization also said that currently , the vietnamese authorities are concerned about the development of the epidemic .
another vietnamese health official pointed out that on the 22 nd , a sister died of serious respiratory tract disease in a hospital in hanoi and the health authorities suspected that the two were also the victims of the bird flu .
millions of poultry meat being infected in indonesia
( agence france - presse , jakarta , 25 th ) - the indonesian ministry of agriculture announced today that the bird flu outbreak has caused millions of dead chickens , but so far no case of human infection has been reported .
the head of the animal department of the ministry of agriculture , suzuki , told the public that no one in indonesia has been infected with the deadly disease .
at present , seven countries in the asian region have reported avian flu cases , and six people in vietnam have died .
indonesian officials said earlier that the bird flu , which was generally infected in java and bali in november last year , was a new city .
a spokesman for the ministry of agriculture said that there is no indication of an outbreak of bird flu in indonesia .
in the evening , he told afp that it was still not clear whether the wave was hatched by a hatch 5nll virus .
most of vietnam 's cases of bird flu deaths were caused by hatch 5n1 virus .
the spokesman said that the new town , together with influenza a - type avian influenza , had caused a death of 4.7 million poultry since november last year .
about 60 percent of them died from illness in the new city .
he said that he had not yet ordered an immediate killing operation .
indonesian state - owned news agency quoted the statement of the indonesian government as saying that the authorities have used british and australian blood to conduct tests to determine the types of the virus , but the results may be the result of the test , and the government will make a report to the relevant international organizations .
snow cover northern europe , causing major traffic and transport chaos
( agence france - presse , paris , 29 th ) - the heavy snow cover half of western europe and northern europe , causing heavy traffic and railway confusion , and forced hundreds of air trips to britain , germany and denmark to be cancelled .
in london , the airport spokesman said that the heavy snow caused more than 200 flight sorties at the airport last night , and 80 flights were suspended early this morning .
the other two airports close to london , including trivial and stalwart , have been affected by snow , and 18 of them have been cancelled due to weather factors .
the frankfurt airport was the largest airport in germany when at least 60 flights were cancelled by the weather in winter .
the transport authorities said that the remaining dozens of flights from frankfurt to frankfurt would have been affected by weather conditions for a whole day .
in france , road traffic restrictions were implemented in paris last night , but similar measures were implemented in other parts of france .
according to the return , the various services of the major airport in paris were close to normal , and the heavy snow and heavy snow caused the delay at the airport yesterday .
however , the paris airport authorities suggested that passengers traveling through air transport should first find out whether their flights should take off and land on time .
in addition to the coast of the country , most areas in france have covered the snow .
