after nixon visited china and the shanghai communique issued seven years ago , the carter administration accepted china 's stand on the taiwan issue and realized the establishment of diplomatic relations between china and the united states .
this incident and deng xiaoping 's successful visit to the united states have opened a new chapter in sino - us relations .
in the early days of reagan 's administration , china and the united states had a fierce confrontation on the taiwan issue .
through arduous negotiations , the two governments issued the famous " august 17 " communique in 1982 , and reached an agreement on resolving the issue of arms sales to taiwan step by step .
the shanghai communique , the sino - us communique on the establishment of diplomatic relations , and the " 17 august " communique have jointly constituted the political cornerstone of sino - us relations .
in the 10 years since the establishment of diplomatic relations , although the two countries have fought on the taiwan issue and other issues , sino - us relations have been stable on the whole , and exchanges and cooperation in various fields have been increasing .
in the 1980 s and early 1990 's , the drastic changes in eastern europe , the disintegration of the soviet union , the end of the cold war , and the most profound changes have taken place in the international situation since world war ii .
the united states has taken the lead in imposing sanctions on china and announced the sale of 150 - 16 fighter planes , linking the issue of human rights with the most favored nation treatment , and allowing lee teng - hui to visit the united states , thus leading to a decline in sino - us relations .
with the rapid development of china 's economy , china 's international status has been constantly enhanced .
more and more people in the united states have realized that the improvement and development of sino - us relations is in the interests of the two countries .
