in the past 30 years , the consumer council has contributed significantly to the protection of consumer rights .
to evaluate the effectiveness of the consumer council 's work , it is best not to see whether the consumer rights and interests have been substantially improved .
i agree with president chen just now that after 30 years , not only the consumers have been clearly aware of their own rights and interests , but also the rights and interests of all sectors of the community are the results of the efforts of the council and the government .
the consumer council conducts regular tests on the products and conducts market surveys and studies on various products and services , and disseminate fair and objective market information to the public through the " choice " monthly digest .
the " selected monthly digest " is deeply trusted by the public , and the current issue of developing the internet version of the " selected monthly digest " will be more effective in giving play to its functions and helping consumers to obtain market information .
the consumer council has 11 regional consumer advisory centres and 16 telephone hotlines which provide information on goods and services to consumers and receive complaints from consumers .
since the establishment of the consumer council , the number of enquiries received by the consumer council has increased from several thousand in the early 1970 s to 146,000 in the early 70 s , an increase of more than 20 times over the previous year .
in addition , the consumer council has handled more than 26,000 complaints this year .
the consumer council will also remind consumers not only of the modus operandi of individual shops , but also of a certain deterrent effect .
