rural education has a broad impact on the overall situation of rural economic and social development .
since the beginning of reform and opening up , tremendous and profound changes have taken place in china 's urban and rural areas , and this is inseparable from the development of education , especially rural education .
the system of contracted responsibility for the production of households in rural areas has greatly emancipated the productive forces .
one of the fundamental reasons for this is that the advanced and practical technology of agriculture has been widely spread . the reason why township and town enterprises have been able to make a large amount of the surplus labor force in the rural areas and cities is that the rural labor force , which has been supported by the compulsory education , has made great achievements in the popularization of compulsory education in rural areas .
at present , china 's agriculture and the rural economy are in a crucial stage of development , and the development of high - quality , high - efficiency , ecological , and security agriculture is developing . the industrialization of agriculture is expanding , and the transfer of surplus labor force in rural areas is urgently needed to comprehensively improve the quality of rural labor force .
the rise of the new scientific and technological revolution in the world and the comprehensive development of a well - off society have set higher demands on the scientific and cultural quality and ideological and moral quality of the broad masses of rural population .
without the comprehensive " universal nine " plan , without the comprehensive improvement of the peasants ' quality , it will be very difficult to achieve a comprehensive well - off life .
we must fully understand the basic , guiding , and overall role of rural education in comprehensively building a well - off society .
