after half a year of controversy , the advance team of the japanese self - defense forces finally went to iraq by the end of 2003 .
this was the first time japan dispatched troops to overseas battlefield since the end of world war ii .
it reflects the will of japan to move toward a political and military power , and also indicates that japan 's defense strategy has begun to change .
the reason why the self - defense forces have made this trip has attracted people 's attention is that it is not an isolated incident .
japan has made a breakthrough in the afghan war by taking advantage of the opportunity of the afghan war , and by taking advantage of the issue of the korean peninsula , it has adopted the " legal system , " and has laid down a precedent for the use of force and even the preemptive strikes for the sdf , and the koizumi cabinet has recently adopted the " basic plan for supporting iraq 's reconstruction , " and has made a start for sending troops to iraq .
this step has finally broken the restrictions imposed by japan 's peace constitution and achieved the goal of sending troops overseas .
in addition , japan is also preparing to revise the " basic defense forces concept " in 2004 so as to legalize the law on sending troops overseas , and to send a " permanent force " to overseas countries .
at the same time , the japanese cabinet meeting also made a decision on the deployment of the missile defense system in early 2004 , and introduced the us - made " standard - 3 " missiles and " patriot - 3 " missiles to intercept the atmosphere and return to the atmosphere .
it is not difficult to see that japan 's self - defense forces are developing in the direction of a regular army with " offensive and defensive capabilities , " and the so - called " self - defense force " seems to have the name of " special defense . "
the reason why japan 's action has attracted people 's attention is , first of all , that these military decisions are an impact on japan 's peace constitution .
