after entering the new century , economic globalization has become a major and severe challenge facing african countries .
the leaders of african countries have more and more clearly realized that africa should not be able to seize the opportunity to seek countermeasures .
on 9 july 2002 , the african union was officially established and put into operation , and on the one hand , african countries have been actively implementing the " new partnership for african development , " striving to extricate themselves from the unfavorable situation in economic globalization as soon as possible , and on the other hand , they have made great efforts to solve the problem of the great cause of the rejuvenation of africa - - - - - - - - - - - - - to create an environment of unity , peace , and stability .
at present , the overall situation in africa has become more relaxed , the hot issue has been noticeably cooling down , and various countries have strengthened their sense of urgency to end armed conflicts .
with the great support of the united nations and the international community , the influential regional organizations , regional big powers , and well - known politicians in africa have taken active action to increase the intensity of resolving regional conflicts and eliminating internal chaos , and the conflict and turbulence that have been basically controlled for many years .
for example , in june last year , the congo ( kinshasa ) set up a government of national unity , and the west of the republic of congo ( the republic of congo ) in july , the government and the anti - government armed forces signed a peace agreement in the ghanaian capital of the republic of the republic of the congo , and the government and the anti-government armed forces in the southern part of the country began the peace process in kenya .
of course , the current situation of stability in the african region is still relatively weak , and the achievements of peace still need to be consolidated , and some potential or practical armed conflicts still need to be finally solved .
at the same time , there is still a great gap between the economic development speed of african countries and the developing countries in asia . all these are unfavorable factors for the development of africa .
how the african countries should effectively cope with the challenges of economic globalization and realize the dream of african rejuvenation still needs the african people to make long - term and arduous efforts .
