as the largest debtor country in the world , the amount of us foreign debts has also increased .
the total amount of debts owed by foreign creditors in the united states amounted to 64.94 trillion dollars by the end of september last year , a 2.2 percent higher than the previous figures .
on average , each american is responsible for the amount of foreign debts of over us $ 20,000 .
it is a trickery that the international monetary fund ( imf ) issued a research report last week , which has sharply sounded the alarm for the us financial base , and pointed out that the us foreign debt , which has been continually breaking through the record , has reached the level of threatening global financial stability .
statistics show that foreign private investors control over 40 percent of us government bonds .
this is not something that can be said to be the first half of the 20 th century , and the measures that the united states has made to the president , namely , the adoption of a deficit policy to stimulate the economy within the country , while the financial loss is to be resolved through foreign debt .
this move played an important role in stimulating the " effective demand " so as to help the rok tide over the economic crisis .
however , people have noticed that many us administrations have been inclined to use this as a " panacea . "
however , since president reagan initiated a tax reduction and expansion in the 1980 s , the us financial deficit has gradually increased and eventually become the biggest debtor country .
