pakistani and indian officials held talks in islamabad from 16 to 18 february , hoping that peace will again rise in the south asian continent .
the agenda and mode of the future talks have been decided by the two countries ' officials , and the establishment of a mechanism for the continued dialogue is an indication of the resumption of the process of the dialogue between the two countries after two years , which has laid a foundation for the gradual settlement of all the remaining issues , including the kashmir dispute , and has embodied the valuable sincerity of the two sides .
before the talks , although the relations between the two countries have been permeated with a series of goodwill moves made by the two sides , most analysts still have a cautious attitude toward the prospects of the peace process .
this is no wonder that looking back at the urgent situation of the relations between pakistan and india over the past few years , it seems that nobody can guarantee : today 's sunshine on the negotiation table will not turn into a sparse of electric shock on the border .
however , on the 18 th , the two countries ' statement , which was read with a smile by the pakistani state secretary of state for foreign affairs , made the optimistic mood of the two countries , and made many people who have been concerned about the situation in south asia .
first of all , the timetable for the talks is very operable , and the two sides have not only clearly defined the time and agenda of the talks , but also stipulated the different levels of talks in accordance with the importance of the discussion .
second , the two sides have drawn lessons from the direct dialogue between the leaders of the two countries , which resulted in the failure of the talks in july 2001 , and adopted a " step - by - step " way of dialogue so that the level of the talks can be carried out from a low level to a high level , so as to make full preparations for the high - level dialogue .
third , after the two countries experienced several twists and turns in bilateral relations , they unanimously said that war is not a good way to resolve disputes , and that the two sides should be far away from war , and this consensus has laid a foundation for the understanding of the leaders of the two countries to reach a " forever no longer war . "
