after the " 911 " incident , us president bush dished out the " preemptive " strategy in june 2002 and put it into practice in us foreign relations , and launched the first " preemptive " war in iraq in march last year .
the " preemptive " concept has not only run counter to the norms of international law with " mutual respect for sovereignty and territorial integrity " as the core , but has also inevitably led to a dangerous effect of mass action , and a new situation of unrest in the international order will arise .
at the beginning of the " preemptive " theory , some us political figures put forward such a question : " if other countries follow the example of what they should do ? "
as a result , in the past two years , more and more countries have claimed to be " preemptive " and the " preemptive " contingent has been expanded .
this is a new trend worth paying attention to and studying .
in the same month when bush put forward his " preemptive " strategy , australian prime minister howard took the first stop to express his support .
he said : once the terrorists are required to attack australia 's reliable intelligence , australia will adopt a " preemptive " strategy and will not hesitate to take military action in neighboring countries .
he even suggested that the " preemptive " principle be written into the united nations charter , and that it is necessary to amend the un charter , so as to give the " preemptive " rights to various countries to crack down on terrorists or countries that support terrorist activities .
in the northeast asian region , the japanese defense agency proposed in its " defense white paper " published in july 1999 that japan can launch a " preemptive strikes " against foreign bases before it is facing missile attacks or military invasion .
after the iraq war , the call for japan 's " preemptive " strategy was even more vociferous .
