in july last year , president bush visited five african countries , including senegal , south africa , botswana , uganda , and nigeria , and promised to provide 15 billion us dollars for the prevention and treatment of aids in african countries , while the other 100 million us dollars were used to crack down on terrorist activities in africa , and announced the food emergency aid program and education aid program .
these aid programs were once welcomed by african countries and have won many praise internationally .
