( international ) silicon valley unemployment rate indicates a recovery in us high - tech industry
xinhua news agency , los angeles , january 19 ( reporter yan liang ) - an influential economic development research organization in the silicon valley in the united states issued a report a few days ago , saying that the unemployment rate in the silicon valley is declining rapidly .
this is a clear signal that the high - tech industry in the region has begun to recover .
in the annual report " the silicon valley economic index 2004 " of the non - profit organization , the unemployment rate between the second quarter of 2002 and the second quarter of 2003 decreased from 10 percent in the previous year to 5 percent .
the report said that with the gradual recovery of high - tech industries , the unemployment rate will continue to decline .
the challenge facing the economic development in the silicon valley is that a large number of highly trained high - tech workers are required to fill new jobs in the future .
the report said that among the high - tech industries in silicon valley , the unemployment rate in the biotechnology industry was the lowest , and the recovery momentum was the most obvious . the number of risk investment in the silicon valley in 2003 was the same as the computer software industry for the first time .
the report said that biotechnology industry will play an increasingly important role in the economic development of the silicon valley .
the report also showed that the average pay of employees in the second quarter of 2002 to the second quarter of 2003 decreased for the third consecutive year , but the decline has dropped from 6 percent in the previous year to 1.5 percent .
silicon valley is still a rich region in the united states , with an average annual salary of 6.24 million us dollars , 60 percent higher than the average of the united states .
however , the level of consumption in this region is 47% higher than that of the whole country .
