( international ) economists predict that the united states is the biggest winner of the us dollar devaluation
xinhua news agency , davos , switzerland , january 23 ( reporter li jie ) - the 34 th annual meeting of the world economic forum , which is being held in davos , switzerland , held a special discussion on the issue of the us dollar devaluation , and some experts predict that the united states will be the biggest winner of the us dollar 's sustained low exchange rate .
most of the economists attending the meeting held that us officials , including us secretary of treasury john garner , seem to have given up the " strong us dollar policy " that has been pursued in recent years .
the us dollar 's low exchange rate will provide greater economic development space and more job opportunities for the united states . this is very obvious in the manufacturing sector .
at the same time , the depreciation of the us dollar has made us products more competitive in the domestic and foreign markets , which will help the united states fill its trade deficit .
however , experts believe that a weak dollar will also have a negative impact on the united states .
first of all , the us stock market may continue to be sluggish , and the value of various kinds of investment may decrease , and foreign investors will be worried about a further decline in the us dollar , and second , import commodities will lead to a decline in the living standards of the americans , and third , the us dollar is likely to trigger trade and financial turmoil .
however , the us dollar 's depreciation will be even more serious in its crackdown on europe , japan , and canada .
after the decline in the us dollar exchange rate , the pressure of european exports increased , and this caused the european economy to be pushed into an all - round recession .
