( international ) japanese exports reach record high in 2003
xinhua news agency , tokyo , january 26 ( by yue shaoyan ) japan 's import and export trade volume reached a record high in 2003 , with a trade surplus of 10.1 trillion yen in three years , according to statistics released by the japanese finance ministry on the 26 th .
in exports , japan 's exports to the united states decreased by 9.8 percent over the previous year , but exports to asia grew by 12.9 percent .
this not only made up some of the decrease in japan 's exports to the united states , but also caused japan 's total exports to increase by 4.7 percent last year to a record 54.598 trillion yen .
in the import of oil and natural gas , japan 's total imports increased by 5 percent over the previous year to 44.202 trillion yen , a record high in the same period .
japan 's trade surplus in 2003 was 10.237 trillion yen , an increase of 3.6 percent over the previous year .
