( international ) the wto has already submitted the " berde subsidies " dispute to arbitration
xinhua news agency , geneva , january 26 ( reporter li jie ) the world trade organization ( wto ) announced on the 26 th that the appeal of the eu and other seven wto members to impose sanctions on the united states on the us has already been submitted to the arbitration institutions .
this sanctions came from the fact that the united states has failed to annul the " burton amendment " within the time limit stipulated by the wto .
the us congress adopted the " bill on the sideline " in 2000 , calling on the us government to make a direct subsidy to us companies that have been fined in the anti - dumping and anti - subsidy cases , and not to hand over to the us department of finance .
this move of the united states has met with opposition from major trading partners , including the eu and japan .
the wto eventually ruled in january 2003 that the amendment violated the global trade rules and demanded that the united states abolish it before december 27 , 2003 .
however , the united states has not implemented the wto 's ruling .
for this reason , the eu , japan , canada , brazil , india , the republic of korea , mexico , and chile recently applied to the wto , asking for permission to levy the amount of tax on some of the products from the united states , which is equivalent to the amount of us government subsidies .
however , the united states subsequently questioned the level of sanctions and the legality of the sanctions .
