( international ) new danish move to restrict immigration
xinhua news agency , stockholm , january 28 , copenhagen news : the danish government submitted a new bill to the parliament on the 28 th to restrict immigration .
under the bill , children born in denmark will no longer have the right to automatically obtain the denmark nationality .
the bill is the latest measure taken by the danish liberal party leader rasmussen since he took office as prime minister in november 2001 .
according to reports , the bill is likely to be passed by the parliament , because the liberal party has won the support of the right - wing people 's party on the issue of migration .
the bill requires foreigners who have been born in denmark to apply for a nationality in the same way as other immigrants , rather than automatically obtaining a nationality .
those who have obtained nationality groups will be deprived of their nationality if they have committed a criminal offence of serious harm to society .
in the past two years , the danish government has introduced a series of measures to restrict immigration , including the issuance of long - term permits and limitations of migrants to denmark .
the number of foreign victims in denmark dropped from 1,4347 in 1993 to 3,500 in 2003 , the government said .
denmark 's image of freedom and human rights has been damaged as a result .
