although the arms race between the two superpowers of the united states and the soviet union has brought the nuclear weapons to the point that the world is sufficient to destroy the whole world , both sides have realized the danger of nuclear war and avoided the button .
after the disintegration of the soviet union and the world entered the post - cold war era , the danger of a large - scale nuclear war was basically eliminated .
at the same time , however , the danger of nuclear proliferation is not reduced , but an increase .
the phenomenon of such proliferation is manifested in two aspects .
first , some countries with considerable resources and strength have , out of the purpose of regional hegemony , confrontation with neighboring countries , and maintaining security or promoting blackmail and diplomacy , in a bid to create and possess nuclear weapons through various means .
the other is a group of non - governmental organizations in some non - countries , especially the extremist islamic forces that have strong hatred for the western world , and they are also trying by every possible means to seek small nuclear weapons , and do not hesitate to hurt a large number of innocent people and carry out bloody terrorist activities in the west .
